{"lemma":"هَشّ","slug":"هَشّ","root":"ه.ش.ش","root_slug":"ه-ش-ش","root_link":"/words/roots/ه-ش-ش","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41189","n41193"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to beat down (leaves, branches)","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"قَالَ هِيَ عَصَايَ أَتَوَكَّأُ عَلَيْهَا وَأَهُشُّ بِهَا عَلَىٰ غَنَمِي وَلِيَ فِيهَا مَآرِبُ أُخْرَىٰ","english":"He said, \"It is my stick. I lean on it, I beat down with it for my sheep, and I have many other uses of it."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to smile; to make a friendly expression","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"عندما وجدته عرّفته بنفسي، فهشّ في وجهي وقال لي إنّه في خدمتي.","english":"When I found him, I made my presence known to him, whereupon he behaved politely towards me and told me he would be in my service."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fragile, crisp"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"cordial, welcoming"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Possibly onomatopoeic."},"ipa":["/haʃ.ʃa/","/haʃʃ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41189","headword_ar":"هَشَّ","root":"h$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yahi$~u","text_ar":"يَهِشُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, TA;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~a","text_ar":"هَشَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", secpers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$i$ota","text_ar":"هَشِشْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaha$~u","text_ar":"يَهَشُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$aA$apN","text_ar":"هَشَاشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, A, Msb, TA) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hu$uw$apN","text_ar":"هُشُوشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hu$uw$N","text_ar":"هُشُوشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~N","text_ar":"هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as appears from what follows];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, soft, yielding, flaccid, flabby, lax, slack, uncompact, crummy, fragile, frangible, brittle, friable, easily"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly broken;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, A, Msb, TA;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna fiyhi raxaAwapN","text_ar":"كَانَ فِيهِ رَخَاوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna rixowFA lay~inFA","text_ar":"كَانَ رِخْوًا لَيِّنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, * TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAna waA@sotaroxaY","text_ar":"لَانَ وَا@سْتَرْخَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~a Alxubozu","text_ar":"هَشَّ الخُبْزُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hu$uw$apN","text_ar":"هُشُوشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~N","text_ar":"هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SAr","text_ar":"صار"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~FA","text_ar":"هَشًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bread became"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy to break."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~a AlEuwdu","text_ar":"هَشَّ العُودُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, Msb,) aor. ["},{"kind":"text","text":", or]"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hu$uw$N","text_ar":"هُشُوشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick, broke in pieces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became easily"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly broken."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~ati Al$~ajarapu","text_ar":"هَشَّتِ الشَّجَرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~N","text_ar":"هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tree dropped its leaves, one after another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb [in which it seems to be indicated that the aor. of the verb in this sense is"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is contr. to rule in an intrans. verb of this class; and I think it improbable.]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~a","text_ar":"هَشَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hu$uw$apN","text_ar":"هُشُوشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became weak; unable to endure difficulty"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~a","text_ar":"هَشَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He affected languor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languidness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takas~ara","text_ar":"تَكَسَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became old,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aged."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~a","text_ar":"هَشَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$i$otu","text_ar":"هَشِشْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaha$~u","text_ar":"يَهَشُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~a","text_ar":"هَشَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$a$otu","text_ar":"هَشَشْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yahi$~u","text_ar":"يَهِشُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$aA$apN","text_ar":"هَشَاشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$aA$N","text_ar":"هَشَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, cheerful, brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he smiled, and was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became cheerful, brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$i$otu bifulaAnK","text_ar":"هَشِشْتُ بِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$a$otu bihi","text_ar":"هَشَشْتُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, cheerful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in behaviour towards such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became cheerful in countenance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joyful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleased, at meeting with such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yaha$~u A_ilaY A_ixowaAnihi","text_ar":"هُوَ يَهَشُّ اـِلَى اـِخْوَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is cheerful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards his brethren"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biY","text_ar":"بِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalotu Ealayohi faA@hota$~a","text_ar":"دَخَلْتُ عَلَيْهِ فَا@هْتَشَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I went in to him, and he was cheerful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his behaviour towards me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ihotaz~a lY","text_ar":"اـِهْتَزَّ لى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$i$otu lilomaEoruwfi","text_ar":"هَشِشْتُ لِلْمَعْرُوفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, TA, *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$a$otu","text_ar":"هَشَشْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$aA$apN","text_ar":"هَشَاشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$aA$N","text_ar":"هَشَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, cheerful, brisk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to do what was kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I desired to do it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ihota$a$otu","text_ar":"اـِهْتَشَشْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"llmErwf","text_ar":"للمعروف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, cheerful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and desirous, to do what was kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa *uw ha$aA$K A_ilaY Alxayori","text_ar":"هُوَ ذُو هَشَاشٍ اـِلَى الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He possesses cheerfulness, briskness, liveliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightliness, of disposition to do good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) Accord. to Sh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$i$otu","text_ar":"هَشِشْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rejoiced, and desired;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, joyful, and desirous."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$i$otu A_ilaY A@moraA^atiY","text_ar":"هَشِشْتُ اـِلَى ا@مْرَاَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", if correct, means either (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I inclined towards my wife,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, brisk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly, in disposition towards her."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And accord to ISd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$aA$u Alqawomi","text_ar":"هَشَاشُ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the TA, but accord. to the JK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$aAhi$u","text_ar":"هَشَاهِشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people's being in a state of commotion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agitation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~a Alwaraqa","text_ar":"هَشَّ الوَرَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sgh, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~N","text_ar":"هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He beat the leaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"with a staff, or stick,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that they might fall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$oha$ahu","text_ar":"هَشْهَشَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Z, TA.) It is said in the Kur, [xx. 19,] (S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^ahu$~u bihaA EalaY ganamiY","text_ar":"وَاَهُشُّ بِهَا عَلَى غَنَمِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I beat the leaves with it in order that they may fall upon my sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, A:) or, accord. to Fr,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and I beat the dry trees with it in order that their leaves may fall so that my sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, may feed upon them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so says As: (TA:) Lth says, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alha$~u","text_ar":"الهَشُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies thy"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drawing towards thee a branch of a tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also, thy"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scattering its leaves towards thee with a staff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, * TA:) but Az says, that the correct ex-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2895},{"kind":"text","text":"planation is that given by Fr and As; not the former of the two explanations given by Lth. (TA.) [The verb also seems to have a similar application in a more extended sense; for it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~a","text_ar":"هَشَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~N","text_ar":"هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies He (a man) assaulted ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAla","text_ar":"صَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":") with his staff, or stick. (Msb.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~a Alha$iyma","text_ar":"هَشَّ الهَشِيمَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke in pieces the dry herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","A","Msb","TA","S","K","IAar","Sgh"]},{"entry_id":"n41193","headword_ar":"هَشٌّ","root":"h$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A thing, (S, Msb,) or anything, (JK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, yielding, flaccid, flabby, lax, slack, uncompact, crummy, fragile, frangible, brittle, friable, easily"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly broken;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, * S, * A, * Msb, K, * TA;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rixowN lay~inN","text_ar":"رِخْوٌ لَيِّنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$iy$N","text_ar":"هَشِيشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK, S, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubozN ha$~N","text_ar":"خُبْزٌ هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$aA$N","text_ar":"هَشَاشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bread that is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy to break."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubozapN ha$~apN","text_ar":"خُبْزَةٌ هَشَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lump of dough, baked in a fire in the ground, that is dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"asserted by IKtt to have two contr. significations. (TA.) [But to this assertion it may be replied, that dry bread is easy to break.] And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^utoruj~apN ha$~apN","text_ar":"اُتْرُجَّةٌ هَشَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A citron easy to break:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwdN ha$~N","text_ar":"عُودٌ هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stick, that is easily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly broken."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa ha$~N","text_ar":"هُوَ هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almakosiri","text_ar":"المَكْسِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, A, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almakosari","text_ar":"المَكْسَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, [but this is contr. to all the other authorities that I know,]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almukas~ari","text_ar":"المُكَسَّرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compliant, when asked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is of easy nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to what is sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"demanded, of him, of things needed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) said in praise of a man (S, TA) when it means [lit.] that he is not one whose wood gives only a sound when one endeavours to produce fire from it; but said in dispraise of a man when it means [lit.] that he is one whose wood is weak. (TA.) [And in like manner] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$iy$N","text_ar":"هَشِيشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haA$~N","text_ar":"هَاشٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) signify (tropical:)  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who rejoices,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is glad, when asked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa haA$N","text_ar":"هُوَ هَاشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda Als~uw^aAli","text_ar":"عِنْدَ السُّوَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$iy$N","text_ar":"هَشِيشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one who rejoices,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is glad, at being asked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN ha$~N","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN ha$~N A_ilaY A_ixowaAnihi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ هَشٌّ اـِلَى اـِخْوَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haA$~N","text_ar":"هَاشٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who is cheerful, brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly, in his behaviour towards his brethren."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN ha$~N ba$~N","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ هَشٌّ بَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who is cheerful, brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful in countenance; pleasant"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therein"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b$","text_ar":"بش"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA bihi ha$~N ba$~N","text_ar":"اَنَا بِهِ هَشٌّ بَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am cheerful, brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly, in behaviour towards him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joyful; happy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN ha$~N fuw^aAduhu","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ هَشٌّ فُوَادُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prompt, to do good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fara$N ha$~u","text_ar":"فَرَشٌ هَشُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEinaAni","text_ar":"العِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse that is brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light of rein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN ha$~N","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse that sweats much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, IF, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaluwdN","text_ar":"صَلُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Slwd","text_ar":"صلود"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","JK","K","A","TA"]}]}}